	<p
		class="max-w-[62ch] text-pretty text-[19px] font-light leading-[1.7] tracking-[-0.005em] text-(--ink-soft)"
	>
		I like owning a problem end to end, not picking up tickets — being in it
		from the first prototype to the number it moves, and sticking around to
		fix what breaks after. The work I'm proudest of is mostly invisible:
		things load faster, fewer things break, people stop noticing the
		interface. Off the clock I read too much about typography and rebuild my
		keyboard firmware more often than I need to.
	</p>
